ivardefs.name: caseSensitive
ivardefs.desc: If code comparison is case sensitive when codes within this system are compared to each other.

ivardefs.name: compositional
ivardefs.desc: True If code system defines a post-composition grammar.

ivardefs.name: concept_
ivardefs.desc: Concepts that are in the code system. The concept definitions are inherently hierarchical, but the definitions must be consulted to determine what the meaning of the hierarchical relationships are.

ivardefs.name: contact_
ivardefs.desc: Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher.

ivardefs.name: content
ivardefs.desc: How much of the content of the code system - the concepts and codes it defines - are represented in this resource.

ivardefs.name: copyright
ivardefs.desc: A copyright statement relating to the code system and/or its contents. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the code system.

ivardefs.name: count
ivardefs.desc: The total number of concepts defined by the code system. Where the code system has a compositional grammar, the count refers to the number of base (primitive) concepts.

ivardefs.name: date
ivardefs.desc: The date  (and optionally time) when the code system was published. The date must change if and when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the code system

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: A free text natural language description of the code system from a consumer's perspective.

ivardefs.name: experimental
ivardefs.desc: A boolean value to indicate that this code system is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing), and is not intended to be used for genuine usage.

ivardefs.name: filter_
ivardefs.desc: A filter that can be used in a value set compose statement when selecting concepts using a filter.

ivardefs.name: hierarchyMeaning
ivardefs.desc: The meaning of the hierarchy of concepts.

ivardefs.name: identifier
ivardefs.desc: A formal identifier that is used to identify this code system when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance.

ivardefs.name: jurisdiction_
ivardefs.desc: A legal or geographic region in which the code system is intended to be used.

ivardefs.name: name
ivardefs.desc: A natural language name identifying the code system. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation.

ivardefs.name: property_
ivardefs.desc: A property defines an additional slot through which additional information can be provided about a concept.

ivardefs.name: publisher
ivardefs.desc: The name of the individual or organization that published the code system.

ivardefs.name: purpose
ivardefs.desc: Explaination of why this code system is needed and why it has been designed as it has.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of this code system. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content.

ivardefs.name: title
ivardefs.desc: A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the code system.

ivardefs.name: url
ivardefs.desc: An absolute URI that is used to identify this code system when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this code system is (or will be) published.

ivardefs.name: useContext_
ivardefs.desc: The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These terms may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate code system instances.

ivardefs.name: valueSet
ivardefs.desc: Canonical URL of value set that contains the entire code system.

ivardefs.name: version
ivardefs.desc: The identifier that is used to identify this version of the code system when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the code system author and is not expected to be globally unique. For exampl

ivardefs.name: versionNeeded
ivardefs.desc: This flag is used to signify that the code system has not (or does not) maintain the definitions, and a version must be specified when referencing this code system.
